<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101248884237998></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101248884237998><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=9&mid=101248884237998>RE: new and would like some help</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=9&mid=101248884237998#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=99264><span id=Scholar>Bilm</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>17 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 31st 10:55 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.41]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, most of your questions are already answered on this board.<br><br>I will have patience and will try to help you.<br><br>You should focus on one char till he hit 40 or 45. You can get equipment / money much better then.<br><br>1) Banded is ok till low / mid 20. After that you can replace it with bronze / ba armor. I've got my first scaled mystic armor in my low 20s. Dunno when you can start totemic. At level 9 you have sow. You can try the run to KC and ask to loot jarsath armor. It's no drop and often rot. At level 9 it will be _very_ dangerous without a leader and invis! I did it in my low 20s.<br><br>2) I had no problems to keep all melee skills maxed till about 43 / 44 (after 44 i've grouped more). For 2HB buy a shovel 4 / 27. Yes, the damage isn't so good but it's fast for 2HB.<br><br>3) Look for bronze, fine steel or velium weapons. Should be ok till 20.<br><br>4) Hm, don't know good armor quest for stuff better then banded at your level.<br><br>5) In the low levels you will just be a healer who can cast sow. The stats buff will let the melee feel better then having a real effect. The 1st slow worth to cast is targar at 29. For regen and canni you have to wait till 24. Just hunt in zones you like (either solo or grouped).<br><br>6) Like most classes shamans starts to shine at 29/30. Druids / Wizards get ports, SKs get FD, Enchanters get clarity, clerics get revive and we get targar. Don't give up. Shamans are a cool class :-).<br><br>Oh, only have gheal for healing from 40-50 sucks! <br><br>Bilm<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
